{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Once the user is authenticated, the ability of a computer to control the access of data and resources by that user is",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : "called access ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "inlineContent" : [
        {
          "text" : "control\/authorisation",
          "type" : "text"
        }
      ],
      "type" : "strong"
    },
    {
      "text" : ". Computers provide access control through a variety of means.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Home",
        "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Computing",
        "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Ethical-Social-Economic-issues"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Authorisation"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Authorisation"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "File-Permissions",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "File Permissions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Most operating systems have settings to control the ability of users to view or make changes to specific files or",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "folders. These settings are called ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "permissions",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "An application of file permissions is when a teacher may set a presentation file to be read-only for students, so",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "they do not accidentally (or intentionally) change its contents.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Typically, users can only change the permissions for any file or folder they own. However, most OSs allow for a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "special user called an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "administrator",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", who can override the permissions for almost any file or folder.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A normal user may also be given special ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "administrator rights",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : " that al- low them to override the permissions for certain",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "files or folders, just like an administrator.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Managing permissions and administrative rights can be a complex task, and it is possible to accidentally grant access",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to a file or administrative rights to an unauthorised user. Such a user can then make use of such mistakes to gain",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "unauthorised access to data and resources.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Authentication for the administrator must be especially strong, as an in- truder that successfully claims to be the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "administrator can bypass file per- missions entirely.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "File permissions do not prevent an intruder with physical access to a storage device from accessing files or folders",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "directly without going through the op- erating system. To prevent such unauthorised access, it is necessary to use encryption.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "File permissions can be used as access control for both computers connected to a network and computers that are not",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "connected to a network, but are shared by multiple users.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Firewalls",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Firewalls",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Computers connected to a network are naturally more susceptible to intru- sion as unauthorised access can occur",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "without the physical presence of an intruder.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Hence, computers connected to a network usually require another layer of access control called a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "firewall",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A firewall is a device\/program that prevents unauthorised access to or from a private network. It works by",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "monitoring each piece of data transmitted through a network. It then either blocks or allows data to pass based",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "on a set of rules configured by an administrator.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When properly configured, a firewall can protect computers within a network from unauthorised access. They can",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "be configured to block the transmission of data (aka ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "traffic",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") between unauthorised senders and receivers, especially",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "requests for data from anonymous users on the Internet. This prevents in- truders from gaining access to the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "computers within a network.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Since firewalls can also block traffic based on the type of application that is transmitting the data, it can",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "also stop certain harmful programs from sending copies of themselves to other computers through the network.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Configuring a firewall correctly can be complex and a misconfigured firewall may have security vulnerabilities",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that allows intruders to gain unauthorised access.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A properly configured firewall allows for a private network (aka ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "intranet",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : ") to be set up such that all external",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "traffic is blocked and only authenticated and authorised users are able to access it. Since the users on a private",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "network are generally trusted and expected to keep information on the network con- fidential, there are usually",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "fewer concerns about unauthorised access when sharing data on a private network.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Conversely, a public network such as the Internet allows anyone to connect to it and share data. Since public",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "networks have little-to-no restrictions, users need to be wary of possible security and privacy risks when accessing it.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Encryption",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Encryption",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Encryption is the process of encoding data so that a secret key is required to read the data. Like passwords, the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "secret key is usually provided as a sequence of bytes.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Before the encrypted data is decoded using the secret key, it appears as random and meaningless data.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Encryption is often used to protect data from unauthorised access by allowing only authorised users to have the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "secret key. It can be used in combination with file permissions so an unauthorised user who bypasses file permissions",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "would still be unable to use the accessed data without knowing the secret key.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Fun fact: A website uses encryption if its address starts with ”https:\/\/” and a padlock icon appears next to its address.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "##f Understanding of Privacy Policies",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Unauthorised access can occur indirectly due to the actions of 3rd-party users or services.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example, a user alters file permissions to let a classmate access some private files. That classmate in turn",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "shares those files with others without the original user’s knowledge.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Privacy - The ability to keep specific data or resources from being known by others.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In many countries, organisations are required by law to public or make available a privacy policy about the rules",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and practices they follow regarding the collection, protection and use of personal or private data provided by users.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Organisations in Singapore are required by the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) to make their privacy",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "policies available upon request.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Example",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "An increasing number of users share personal information such as photos and location data using online services,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "many of them are unfamiliar with the relevant privacy policies or how such sharing habits may indirectly result",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "in unauthorised access. A poor understanding of the privacy policies of these services can often result in unauthorised",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "access.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Social-Networking-Sites",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Social Networking Sites",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Social networking sites such as Twitter, Instagram and TikTok allow users to share photographs and information quickly",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "with their families and friends. They can also be used to promote businesses or raise awareness of campaigns or causes",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and spread disinformation to clueless people",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "However, these sites can pose many privacy concerns because most users do not read or consider the repercussions of the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "privacy policies used by these sites regarding personal information such as status updates, notes, photographs and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "location data.2",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The privacy policies for many social networking sites do not guarantee that personal data collected will never be exposed",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to unauthorised users and may even require that your personal data be shared with advertisers in order to use their",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "sites. Hence, personal data can potentially be harvested for spam and other threats to privacy that users did not",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "authorise directly.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Remember: Once data is digitised and uploaded to a public network such as the Internet, it can potentially remain there",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "forever (Wayback Machine go brr), since it can be easily copied and republished in ways no longer under the control of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the original uploader.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Oh, and also some privacy policies for some social networking sites don’t guarantee that their personal data will be",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "deleted from the site completely or immediately even after their account is closed, deleted, or has all personal data",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "removed from it.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Personal data is sensitive and should not be shared publicly. Some companies may reject candidates after reviewing",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the information and photographs posted on their social networking accounts, even if this was posted while they were",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "still at school. This is especially important since SST students are, you know, SST students.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To prevent unauthorised access when using social networking sites:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Read and fully understand the privacy policy of the social networking site.3",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Set sharing settings to ”private” so only people you know in real life can read your posts.4",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Think twice before posting personal photographs or information that you may feel uncomfortable sharing.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Accept friend requests wisely. Make sure you know everyone in your friends list.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "If you want to continue shitposting on the internet for whatever reason, I’d advise to create an account that has",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "little-to-no correlation or evidence about your identity.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
